description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Biomedical Scientist &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic individual to join the Cellular Pathology Department as a Specialist Biomedical Scientist. Applications are invited from Biomedical Scientists who are HCPC registered and ideally have post registration experience within Cellular Pathology. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Once competent the post holder will be required to work Saturday and to participate in the on call rota.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department provides a Histopathology and Cytology service for Leeds Teaching Hospitals Trust. We have one permanent full time post based at St James University Hospital, but you may be required to rotate to other sites and sections. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The department is well equipped, fully computerised, accredited to ISO15189 and is acrredited by the IBMS as a training laboratory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We process circa 56,000 surgical cases, 2,000 autopsy cases, and 5000 non-gynaecological cytology cases per annum. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is suitable for someone who is highly motivated, enthusiastic and a good team worker. Experience of histology laboratory techniques is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If we have not contacted you within four weeks of the closing date, we regret to advise you that you have not been selected for interview on this occasion. We are sorry to disappoint you, but hope this will not deter you from applying for any future vacancies that may be of interest to you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
